WorkItem.Description:
Hi,
Excel can handle some vector formats (SVG/EPS/EMF) so we can easily put vector graphs in a file.
I wonder if we can add vector support in phpexcel alongside with raster images without changing the general structure like below

```
$objDrawing = new PHPExcel_Worksheet_Drawing();
$objDrawing->setName('PHPExcel logo');
$objDrawing->setDescription('PHPExcel logo');
$objDrawing->setPath('./images/chart.svg'); //svg file
$objDrawing->setHeight(36);
$objDrawing->setCoordinates('D24');
$objDrawing->setOffsetX(10);
$objDrawing->setWorksheet($objPHPExcel->getActiveSheet());
```
